This is the first slice of GD32F10x (F101/F103/F105/F107) support for
libopencm3. The F10x family is register-compatible with STM32F1 for the
peripherals included here, so this PR adds the stub directories and
forwarders without duplicating any driver code.

Empirically validated by regtrace v0.5: TIM1 + IWDG register-write traces
captured from the GigaDevice F10x SPL match the libopencm3 stm32/common
drivers byte-for-byte in `final_state` mode. Cross-checked against:
- libopencm3 stm32/f0, stm32/f1, stm32/f4
- GigaDevice SPL F10x and F1x0
- STMicro Cube LL stm32f1
All 15 cross-impl pairs match for both vectors. Decision documents and
goldens at:
  https://github.com/<...>/regtrace/blob/main/decisions/v0.5/TIMER.md
  https://github.com/<...>/regtrace/blob/main/decisions/v0.5/IWDG.md

What this PR adds:
- include/libopencm3/gd32/f10x/{memorymap,timer,iwdg,rcc,doc-gd32f10x}.h
- lib/gd32/f10x/Makefile (OBJS: timer_common_all.o + iwdg_common_all.o)
- GD32F10X branch in include/libopencm3/{gd32,stm32}/memorymap.h dispatchers
- GD32F10X branch in include/libopencm3/stm32/{timer,iwdg,rcc}.h dispatchers

`make TARGETS=gd32/f10x lib` builds cleanly. STM32 targets are unaffected
(the new dispatcher branches are only taken when -DGD32F10X is set).

What this PR does NOT add (deferred to follow-up PRs as their share-or-
split decisions are made empirically): GPIO, USART, DMA, I2C, ADC, SPI,
FLASH dedicated GD32F10x sources. The rcc.h forwarder to stm32/f1/rcc.h
is provisional pending an explicit RCC vector and decisions/<v>/RCC.md.
